<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Service Continuity Notes</title>
  <style>
    {{{print_css}}}

    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 12mm;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      color: #1f1635;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .hero,
    .check-card,
    .warning-box,
    .note-box {
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 1em 1.1em;
      margin-bottom: 0.9em;
    }

    .hero {
      background: #faf8ff;
      border-color: #ddd6fe;
    }

    .chip {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 0.45em;
      padding: 0.18em 0.55em;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      background: #ede9fe;
      color: #4c1d95;
    }

    h1,
    h2,
    h3 {
      color: #231942;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0 0 0.25em 0;
      font-size: 18pt;
    }

    h2 {
      margin: 1em 0 0.55em 0;
      font-size: 12pt;
    }

    h3 {
      margin: 0 0 0.35em 0;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
    }

    p {
      margin: 0.3em 0;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 0.45em 0 0 1.1em;
      padding: 0;
    }

    li {
      margin: 0.35em 0;
    }

    .warning-box {
      background: #fff7ed;
      border-color: #fed7aa;
    }

    .muted {
      color: #6b7280;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="chip">{{pack_title}}</div>
    <h1>Service Continuity</h1>
    <p><strong>This claim relies on the same service record created in Stage 1.</strong></p>
    <p>Keep the served notice, service method, and certificate of service aligned as one continuous file.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="check-card">
    <h2>Check</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Notice date matches across the Section 8 notice, N215, and court forms.</li>
      <li>Service method matches the method actually used.</li>
      <li>N215 reflects the real date, address, and recipient used for service.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="warning-box">
    <h2>Failure risk</h2>
    <p>If the notice date, service method, or service evidence do not align, the claim may be challenged or delayed.</p>
    <p class="muted">Treat service continuity as part of the possession claim, not as a separate administrative note.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="note-box">
    <h2>What to keep together</h2>
    <p>Keep the served notice copy, the certificate of service, any postal or hand-delivery evidence, and the updated arrears schedule in the same file.</p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
